HEADWORD: ceratopsian
<hw>ceratopsian</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any of several four-footed
herbivorous horned dinosaurs with enormous beaked skulls, of the late
Cretaceous in North America and Mongolia.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> horned dinosaur.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

